02/12/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The World Bank's vice president for Europe and Central Asia, Shigeo Katsu, urged Macedonia on Wednesday (1 December) to implement structural reforms. He noted the progress made in maintaining macroeconomic stability but said that further reforms were needed to make the economy competitive and flexible. 
In other news Wednesday, Skopje confirmed that Macedonia and Greece would resume talks on their name dispute next Monday. International mediator Matthew Nimitz will oversee the negotiations. (Macedonian Radio, MIA - 01/12/04) 
